abstract: The great storm is over and we have mild weather again. The marine losses along the lakes have been heavy--much larger than during any storm we have had for years. The western part of this State and Iowa have a covering of from twelve to eighteen inches on a level.

Of these nine were caused by kerosene, sixteen by carelessness of occupants and employes, one by defective fine, four by overheated stoves, five were unknown, one was of incendiary origin, and the remainder originated from a variety of accidental causes.

abstract: ALBANY, Dec. 30.--The Governor's Message is completed and nearly all in type. The reports of the Comptroller and Auditor are also nearly ready for delivery, and will also be furnished in advance.
